boxpilot (0.1.1-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Bug-fix release covering the four issues filed against v0.1.0:
    - boxpilotd: create cores_dir before promote rename so install /
      adopt succeed on a fresh machine where /var/lib/boxpilot/cores/
      does not yet exist (#6).
    - boxpilotd: canonicalize all path components before the §6.5 trust
      check so the spec-recommended core_path
      /var/lib/boxpilot/cores/current/sing-box (with `current` as a
      symlink ancestor) passes verification (#7).
    - boxpilotd: validate install-state.json schema_version at startup
      and refuse mutating IPC verbs on mismatch; surface the version
      via service.status so the GUI can show a single banner rather
      than collecting per-action failures (#8).
  * docs: rewrite §11.3 to acknowledge that SagerNet no longer
    publishes upstream checksums; document that
    install-source.json::upstream_sha256_match is reserved and v1.0
    integrity rests on TLS + GitHub asset immutability + post-install
    audit via the recorded SHA256 (#9).

 -- Conn Johnson <johnson.connor.97815@gmail.com>  Fri, 01 May 2026 12:00:00 +0000

boxpilot (0.1.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial Debian package.
  * Plans #1-#8 ship together as v0.1.0:
    - skeleton + helperd, managed core, managed service, profile store,
      activation pipeline, legacy sing-box.service handling, GUI shell,
      diagnostics export with schema-aware redaction.
  * Plan #9: install / upgrade / remove / purge wired through dpkg
    maintainer scripts; D-Bus helper now activated via systemd.

